(42, 7, 39, 12, 5, 20, 20, 'she is a sinner', 'Judgment of Sinners', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment towards sinners. In both passages, the characters express disdain for those deemed sinful, with the Pharisee judging the woman and Gehazi judging Naaman''s lack of reward.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
