(42, 7, 40, 42, 5, 22, 22, 'answering said unto him', 'Perception of Thoughts', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' ability to perceive thoughts. In Luke 7:40, He responds to Simon, while in Luke 5:22, He addresses the thoughts of others. This connection highlights Jesus'' insight into human hearts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 40, 42, 5, 31, 31, 'Jesus answering said unto', 'Connection of Healing and Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' role as a teacher and healer. In Luke 7:40, Jesus engages Simon with a lesson, while in Luke 5:31, He highlights the need for healing among the sick, indicating His mission to address spiritual and physical needs.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 40, 43, 3, 2, 2, 'say on', 'Recognition of Jesus'' Authority', 'This connection highlights the acknowledgment of Jesus as a teacher. In both passages, individuals express a desire to learn from Jesus, indicating his recognized authority. Simon invites Jesus to speak, while Nicodemus acknowledges Jesus'' divine connection.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 40, 43, 13, 13, 13, 'Master', 'Authority of Jesus as Master', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' authority. In both passages, Jesus is addressed as ''Master,'' emphasizing His role as a teacher and leader.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 40, 39, 1, 6, 6, 'Master, say on', 'Honor and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of honor and authority present in both passages. In Luke, Jesus addresses Simon as ''Master,'' reflecting the respect due to authority, while Malachi emphasizes the expectation of honor towards God as Father and Master.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
